column23: Comments
Sending 50mg for next visit
Improved but will give 100mg prior to next visit
Will send 100mg prior to next visit
No need for gaba this visit
Was still too fractious at previous appts on 100mg. used to get full sedation for BW/annual on 200mg. was at least able to get blood and urine for senior panel without full sedation. Improvement!
No need for gaba. Good boy!
Would try 100mg for next visit
O will try to get more gabapentin into cat next time since they didn't get full dose
Previously was very aggressive and would lunge and bite with no provocation. Slightly hissed with vaccination, otherwise did well
This was this cat's first visit at our clinic. We drew blood, gave injections, and took xrays + was able to be done as long as she had cat muzzle on.
Has been here 3x in a short time and sick of us. Was here for surgery but was sick, better now (sick wise, still angry) and went through with spay and declaw today.
Had a dental between visits that caused anxiety for this appointment. Recommended meds in the future
Putting on gabapentin for car ride to move
Putting on gabapentin for car ride to move
Presented for urinating outside litter box. Has history of urinary infections. No behavioral issues noted from previous visits. Diagnosed with UTI today.
Old, grumpy cat. Has been this way for years.
Vocalized while drawing blood. Presented for declaw procedure. Have never seen her previously.
Presentedfor neuter procedure. Was hiding prior to and after surgery. other behaviors caused by restraint for sedation. Recommended gabapentin prior to next visit
Presented for neuter procedure. Have not seen previously. Hissed a little bit when restrained for sedation.
He presented for bloodwork. During blood draw, he did very well. We have never had issues with his behavior.
Timid, but once he gets attention, he opens up and melts
Has been fractious since a kitten, have tried gaba and at highest dose and doesn't touch her. Sedate for everything.
Very unhappy in house, plan to make her a barn cat
Been difficult previous appointments to point sedation is needed to get blood. Today tried to get blood but not greatest physical exam due to wrapped in towel and muzzle.
We increased dose to 300mg as cat still wanted to lunge and bite.
